class Solution {
    public List<String> findRepeatedDnaSequences(String s) {
        int[] count = new int[1 << 21];
        int temp = 0;
        char[] str = s.toCharArray();
        List<String> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < str.length; i++) {
            temp <<= 2;
            char current = str[i];
            switch (current) {
                case 'A':
                    temp |= 1;
                    break;
                case 'C':
                    temp |= 2;
                    break;
                case 'G':
                    temp |= 3;
                    break;
                case 'T':
                    temp |= 4;
                    break;
            }
            if (i >= 9) {
                if (++count[temp] == 2) {
                    ans.add(s.substring(i - 9, i + 1));
                }
                temp &= (1 << 18) - 1;
            }

        }
        return ans;
    }
}
